HEADWORD: Inhabitativeness
<hw>In*hab"it*a*tive*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Phrenol.)</fld> <def>A tendency or propensity to permanent
residence in a place or abode; love of home and country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inhabited</ent>⟦br⟧
